   Undergraduate Summer Jobs Program

   The Summer Undergraduate Jobs Program at SAIC Frederick are full-time
   (40 hours per week) paid positions designed to provide undergraduate
   students of science with firsthand laboratory experience under the
   guidance of a senior researcher. Outstanding students interested in
   pursuing careers in the biological, chemical, and pharmaceutical
   sciences are invited to apply.

   SAIC Frederick also offers summer job opportunities for students
   pursuing undergraduate degrees in the computer sciences, engineering,
   accounting, finance, contracts, logistics, and human resources.

   This programs duration is approximately 10 - 12 weeks, beginning in
   May or June, and flexible to the students vacation schedule from
   school. Applicants must be U.S. Citizens or Permanent Residents.

   Applications for the Summer Undergraduate Jobs Program are accepted
   each year between January 1 and March 15.

   To apply, mail the completed application form (in Adode Acrobat
   format), letter(s) of reference, resume, and college transcript to:

   SAIC Frederick
   Human Resources
   NCI-Frederick
   P.O. Box B
   Frederick, MD 21702-1201

   or e-mail: hr@mail.ncifcrf.gov.
